messages.content:
@gregor I saw that you have added many helpful conditional methods to the o1js. 

Is it possible to use one of those methods to conditionally call the method of another contract in such a way that the Account Update will not be created (similar to `AccountUpdate.createIf()`) and the contract should not be compiled if the condition for calling it is false?

I understand that now I can consume the result of the call with `Provable.if()`, but if I do so, the AccountUpdate will be created in any case, and the contract that I call should be compiled.
